08485nam a22010935i 9783110524499DE-B159720221004111318.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221004t20182018gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2018934561  a97831105244997 a10.1515/97831105244992doi  a(DE-B1597)473961  a(OCoLC)1037980223  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE00aHQ766b.C5222 2018. 4aHQ766 7aHIS0370702bisacsh0483ua304.6660940904qDE-101223/ger00aChildren by Choice? :bChanging Values, Reproduction, and Family Planning in the 20th Century /ced. by Ann-Katrin Gembries, Theresia Theuke, Isabel Heinemann. 1aMünchen ;aWien : bDe Gruyter Oldenbourg, c[2018] 4c©2018  a1 online resource (240 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aWertewandel im 20. Jahrhundert ,x2366-9446 ;v300tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction: Children by Choice? Changing Values, Reproduction, and Family Planning in the 20th Century -- tBirth Control as a National Threat? Pronatalist Discourses on Abortion in France and Germany (1920s–1970s) -- t“Children by Choice” – Family Decisions and Value Change in the Campaigns of the American Planned Parenthood Federation (1942–1973) -- t“Respect girls as future mothers”: Sex Education as Family Life Education in State Socialist Hungary (1950s–1980s) -- tPopular Medical Discourses on Birth Control in the Soviet Union during the Cold War: Shifting Responsibilities and Relational Values -- tParadox of the Pill: Oral Contraceptives in Spain and Poland (1960s–1970s) -- tThe Influence of American Sexual Studies on the ‘Sexual Revolution’ of Italian Women -- tDiscourses on Abortion and their Impact on Institutions in Czechoslovakia and the Czech Republic in the Second Half of the 20th Century (1950–2003) -- tNarratives about Contraception and Abortion in the GDR (1972–1990) Caught between a Liberal Law, Normative Ways of Living and the Individualization of Family Planning -- tFrom “Children by Choice” to “Families by Choice”? 20th-Century Reproductive Decision-Making between Social Change and Normative Transitions -- tAuthors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDuring the 20th century, medico-technical advances such as the invention of the latex condom (1930), the arrival of the contraceptive pill on the free market (1960/61) and the birth of the first child conceived by in vitro fertilization (1978) contributed to the fact that in Europe and the USA, the planning, conceiving and making of children was increasingly perceived as a matter of individual and collective decision-making. Especially since mid-century, these societies underwent profound political, economic and cultural evolutions. In the realm of human reproduction the relationship between the possible, the desirable, and the permitted had to be continually renegotiated. This volume examines in nine chapters how thinking, speaking and acting changed with regards to reproduction and family planning throughout the modern and post-modern period. Applying an international comparative perspective, the study specifically focuses on the role of value changes underlying these transformation processes.  aMedizinisch-technische Errungenschaften des 20. Jahrhunderts, wie beispielsweise die Erfindung des Latex-Präservativs (1930), die Einführung der Anti-Baby-Pille (1961) auf dem freien Markt und die Geburt des ersten durch In-vitro-Fertilisation gezeugten Kindes (1978) führten in Europa und den USA dazu, dass das Planen, Zeugen und Machen von Kinder zunehmend Gegenstand individueller und gesellschaftlicher Auseinandersetzungen wurde. Vor dem Hintergrund umfassender politischer, ökonomischer und kultureller Transformationen musste dabei das Verhältnis zwischen Machbarem, Wünschenswertem und Erlaubtem gesellschaftlich immer wieder neu ausgehandelt werden. Der vorliegende Band untersucht in acht Beiträgen, wie sich im 20. Jahrhundert das Denken, Reden und Handeln im Hinblick auf Kinder und Familienplanung veränderte. In einer international vergleichenden Perspektive wird dabei insbesondere der diesen Entwicklungen zugrunde liegende Wertewandel in den Blick genommen.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aBirth controly20th centuryxHistoryvCongresses. 0aBirth controly20th centuryxHistory. 0aContraceptiony20th centuryxHistoryvCongresses. 0aContraceptiony20th centuryxHistory. 0aFamily planningy20th centuryxHistoryvCongresses. 0aFamily planningy20th centuryxHistory. 0aFertility, Humany20th centuryxHistoryvCongresses. 0aFertility, Humany20th centuryxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh1 aBalestracci, Fiammetta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDudová, Radka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGembries, Ann-Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGembries, Ann-Katrin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeinemann, Isabel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinemann, Isabel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHilevych, Yuliya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIgnaciuk, Agata, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoesch, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSato, Chizu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTheuke, Theresia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTheuke, Theresia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTorenz, Rona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVarsa, Eszter, econtributor.4ctb